Content: Objective: Interactive map that shows the present situation. Clickable events show tooltips with additional information and zoom in one location, as well as marking the event on the overall graph. After seeing present situation, user can then have control over all variables that are a part of the situation. Goal for the user to to adjust the variables to achieve a decrease in carbon levels after a certain amount of years in the future. Accompanying graph and data table will help show result

Content:
You should create a mobile app that classifies sms texts as worth reading, not worth reading.

Use a naive bayes classifier.
http://sebastianraschka.com/Articles/2014_naive_bayes_1.html
Use features like text length, who sent it, average word length, wether or not it has attatchments, what time it was sent etc.

Then have the user categorize his sms history under two classes:
"Worth my time", and "Not Worth my time" to train the classifier.
